2017;;Three Summers;;Australian;;Ben Elton;;Robert Sheehan, Rebecca Breeds, Jacqueline McKenzie;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Three_Summers;;The film's main plotline revolves around a blossoming romance between its two leads, pretentious theremin player Roland (Robert Sheehan) and down-to-earth pub band fiddler Keevy (Rebecca Breeds)<br><br>The film also had a subplot about a racist bigot (played by Michael Caton) meeting a refugee boy and a group of indigenous folk dancers and learns the error of his ways.<br><br>The film contains several running gags, revolving around feminist singer Diamond and her renditions of classic Australian songs and poems and a stern security guard who upholds the rules.